data.title: News from California, across the nation and world
data.meta_description: The L.A. Times is a leading source of breaking news, entertainment, sports, politics, and more for Southern California and the world.
data.text:
Doctors and scientists are keeping an eye on yet another coronavirus subvariant  XEC  that could surpass the latest hyperinfectious strain.

Amid tense, closed-door negotiations, the governor and Democratic lawmakers have released a suite of seven bills that aim to reduce Californians soaring energy costs.

Mayor Karen Bass read that Norm Langer was thinking of closing his deli, so she stopped by for lunch and vowed to address neighborhood problems

The California Department of Food and Agriculture said Thursday that H5N1 bird flu is suspected to have infected three dairy herds in the state.

With an EP on the horizon and upcoming tour dates in Europe, the Maras frontwoman, Mara Zardoya, speaks about the realities of touring a breakup album.

If Tyler Glasnow manages to come back from injury before the playoffs start, will he be the reliable, dominant arm the Dodgers need to win the World Series?
